  "title": "Student Care Teacher/ Subject Specialist (Central & East)",
  "description": "<h3>📒We are looking for a caring and passionate Student Care Teacher to join our team! 🖋️</h3><p></p><p><strong>Why Join Us?</strong></p><p><ul><li><strong>Be part of a supportive and friendly team</strong></li><li><strong>Make a real difference in children’s learning and development</strong></li><li><strong>Opportunities for professional growth and training</strong></li><li><strong>Attractive and competitive benefits and salary</strong></li></ul><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong>Working Hours: </strong>Monday - Friday (Office Hours)<br /><strong>Working Locations: </strong>Central & East (Near MRT stations)<br /><strong>Benefits:</strong> AWS/PB and Medical<br /><strong>Gross Salary:</strong> $3600 (Basic up to $3200)<br /></p></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><ul><li>Create a safe, supportive, and nurturing environment for primary school students after school</li><li>Guide and assist students with homework, providing encouragement and academic support (In any subject)</li><li>Plan and lead fun, engaging, and meaningful enrichment and recreational activities</li><li>Foster positive social skills, good behaviour, and confidence in every child</li><li>Build strong relationships with students, parents, and colleagues to support each child’s growth and wellbeing</li><li>Maintain accurate attendance records and support day-to-day centre operations</li></ul><p></p></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p><ul><li><strong>Minimum a Diploma in any studies</strong></li><li><strong>Confident in teaching any subject to P1 - P6 students</strong></li><li>Genuine care and patience for working with children</li><li>Experience with primary school students is an advantage</li><li>Responsible, proactive, and able to manage a group of students effectively</li><li>Comfortable assisting with homework and guiding learning</li></ul></p><p><br />Interested applicants can send your latest updated resume to felix@talentsatwork.sg or apply directly through the platform. We will be happy to schedule an exploratory call with you.<br /></p><p>Talents@Work Pte Ltd (21C0501)<br />Felix Tan Chin Kuang (R25158946)</p>",
